1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,280
Hello, English learners.
你好，英语学习者。

2
00:00:03,280 --> 00:00:05,200
Welcome back to EnglishPod.
欢迎回到EnglishPod。

3
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,200
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

4
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:07,200
And I'm Erika.
我是Erika。

5
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,120
We're bringing you an advanced lesson today.
今天我们带来了一节高级课程。

6
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:11,120
That's right.
没错。

7
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:14,360
An advanced lesson where we talk about investing in emerging markets.
一节关于投资新兴市场的高级课程。

8
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:15,360
Right.
对。

9
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:17,160
So it's kind of a business topic.
所以这算是一个商业话题。

10
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:19,880
It's kind of a world topic as well.
也算是一个世界性话题。

11
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:20,880
Yes.
是的。

12
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:21,880
And it's pretty difficult.
而且相当难。

13
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:22,880
Yeah.
嗯。

14
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:23,880
It is really hard.
确实很难。

15
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:24,880
Right.
对。

16
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:28,640
So if you're listening and you don't understand everything, please don't get discouraged.
所以如果你在听，但没完全听懂，请不要气馁。

17
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:31,120
Don't worry about it because we're here to learn.
别担心，因为我们是来学习的。

18
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:32,120
Yes.
是的。

19
00:00:32,120 --> 00:00:33,120
And we're here to help you.
我们是来帮助你的。

20
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,120
Right.
对。

21
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,520
So let's get started with this.
那我们开始吧。

22
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:36,840
I'm really excited about this lesson.
我对这节课真的很兴奋。

23
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:37,840
Yeah.
嗯。

24
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:38,840
Okay.
好的。

25
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:39,840
Well, Marco, maybe you can tell us a little bit.
那么，Marco，也许你可以跟我们说说。

26
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,480
What is an emerging market?
什么是新兴市场？

27
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:46,040
An emerging market is a market that is starting to develop.
新兴市场是一个刚开始发展的市场。

28
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:47,040
Okay.
好的。

29
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:48,040
And it's growing rapidly.
而且它增长迅速。

30
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:50,760
So you can maybe give some examples of emerging market.
所以你可以举一些新兴市场的例子。

31
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:53,240
Well, for example, China is an emerging market.
嗯，例如，中国就是一个新兴市场。

32
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:54,240
Yeah.
嗯。

33
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:56,200
In the last years, it's been growing rapidly.
在过去几年里，它一直在快速增长。

34
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:59,560
More and more people are moving to the middle class and have money to spend.
越来越多的人进入中产阶级，有了可支配收入。

35
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:00,560
Right.
对。

36
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:01,560
Exactly.
正是如此。

37
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:03,560
So China is like a really great example of an emerging market.
所以中国是一个很好的新兴市场例子。

38
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:04,560
All right.
好的。

39
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:07,880
Well, with that, let's listen to the dialogue for the first time.
那么，接下来我们第一次听对话。

40
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:20,880
Dad, I'd like to borrow some money.
爸爸，我想借点钱。

41
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:22,040
Sure, Johnny.
当然，约翰尼。

42
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,040
How much do you need?
你需要多少钱？

43
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:24,040
Five bucks?
五块钱？

44
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,040
Come on, Dad.
别这样，爸爸。

45
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,040
I need $30,000.
我需要三万美元。

46
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,800
I want to get into the market.
我想进入市场。

47
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:31,600
You know, I'm tired of hearing all this news about the economic downturn, the inevitable
你知道吗，我已经听腻了那些关于经济衰退、不可避免的

48
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:34,360
recession, people stuffing their money in their mattresses.
萧条，以及人们把钱塞在床垫下的新闻。

49
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,240
I look at this as an opportunity.
我把这看作是一个机会。

50
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:38,720
This is a chance for me to get a jumpstart on building my nest egg.
这是我开始积累养老金的好机会。

51
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,240
I don't know about that.
我可不太确定。

52
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:43,440
With all the uncertainty in the markets right now, it would be a very unwise decision to
现在市场充满不确定性，投资是

53
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:44,440
invest.
非常不明智的决定。

54
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:48,560
I don't know if you're aware, son, but there has been a lot of turmoil in the markets recently.
儿子，我不知道你是否意识到，最近市场动荡很大。

55
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:53,840
There have already been half a million layoffs in the last few months, and we have no idea
过去几个月已经有五十万人失业，我们完全不知道

56
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:57,480
how the proposed stimulus package will impact upon the economy.
拟议的经济刺激计划会对经济产生什么影响。

57
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:59,000
There's just too much instability.
太不稳定了。

58
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,800
I just wouldn't feel comfortable investing in this climate.
在这种环境下投资，我会觉得很不踏实。

59
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,560
But look at it this way.
但你可以这样看。

60
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,960
Every challenge is an opportunity.
每个挑战都是机遇。

61
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:08,520
And anyway, I'm not talking about investing in the domestic market.
而且，我说的不是投资国内市场。

62
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,880
There are emerging markets that promise great returns.
有些新兴市场能带来丰厚回报。

63
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,200
Look at China, for example.
比如中国。

64
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:17,040
They have 1.4 billion people, half a billion of whom have recently entered the middle class.
他们有十四亿人口，其中五亿人最近进入了中产阶级。

65
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:20,880
Here alone, the aggregate demand for consumer goods represents an amazing wealth-generating
仅就这里而言，消费品的总需求就代表着

66
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:21,880
opportunity.
一个巨大的财富创造机会。

67
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:25,040
Oh, come on, son, you're looking at this too naively.
哦，得了吧，儿子，你把这事想得太天真了。

68
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:29,040
The Chinese market has exhibited a great deal of instability, and their currency has been
中国市场表现出很大的不稳定性，而且他们的货币

69
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:31,440
devalued by almost a whole percentage point.
几乎贬值了一个百分点。

70
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:32,440
Fine, then.
那好吧。

71
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:34,520
If that's the way you feel, so be it.
如果你这么想，那就这样吧。

72
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,720
But you're losing out on a great opportunity here.
但你正在错过一个绝佳的机会。

73
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:49,720
I'm going to hit up mom for the cash.
我去找妈妈要钱。

74
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:54,320
Well, it sounds like the dad has missed out on a really big investment opportunity, hey?
嗯，听起来爸爸错过了一个很大的投资机会，是吧？

75
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:57,440
Yeah, and his son is pretty smart.
是啊，他儿子挺聪明的。

76
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,920
Pretty smart little boy.
挺聪明的小家伙。

77
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:03,000
Okay, so we have some great words that we want to look at here.
好了，我们有一些很棒的词要学习。

78
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,920
Why don't we start with the first one, turmoil.
我们先从第一个开始，turmoil。

79
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:06,920
Turmoil.
Turmoil。

80
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:07,920
Turmoil.
动荡。

81
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:08,920
Turmoil.
动荡。

82
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:12,720
So we have some great examples of how turmoil is used in different sentences.
所以我们有一些很好的例子，展示了“动荡”在不同句子中的用法。

83
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:15,040
So let's listen.
那我们来听听。

84
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:23,320
Example one, with a civil war, a famine, and inflation, the country has been in turmoil
例子一：由于内战、饥荒和通货膨胀，这个国家已经处于动荡之中

85
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:29,760
for ten years.
十年了。

86
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:37,160
Example two, there's been a lot of turmoil in my life recently.
例子二：最近我的生活经历了很多动荡。

87
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,840
I've moved to a new city.
我搬到了一个新城市。

88
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,200
I've changed my job.
我换了工作。

89
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:46,800
I broke up with my girlfriend.
我和女朋友分手了。

90
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:58,760
Example three, the devaluation of the dollar caused a great deal of turmoil in the markets.
例子三：美元贬值导致市场出现巨大动荡。

91
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:01,640
So turmoil is a state of...
所以动荡是一种状态……

92
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:05,120
Of uncertainty, of change, of difficult times.
一种不确定、变化、困难时期的状态。

93
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,120
A little bit of chaos.
有点混乱。

94
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,600
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
对，对，对。

95
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:11,440
So for example, when there's a lot of turmoil in the market, that means stock prices are
所以例如，当市场出现很多动荡时，意味着股票价格

96
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:14,080
changing drastically from day to day.
每天都在剧烈变化。

97
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,720
Right, or the economy is in turmoil.
没错，或者经济处于动荡之中。

98
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,760
There's a lot of problems going on.
有很多问题在发生。

99
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:19,760
Yeah, uncertainty.
是的，不确定性。

100
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:20,760
Uncertainty.
不确定性。

101
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:21,760
Okay, good word.
好的，好词。

102
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:27,040
All right, and we also saw something really interesting in the dialogue about a proposed
好的，我们在对话中还看到了一些非常有趣的内容，关于一项提议的

103
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,320
stimulus package.
刺激计划。

104
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:31,560
A proposed stimulus package.
一项提议的刺激计划。

105
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:35,360
So a proposed stimulus package is something that's going on now.
所以一项提议的刺激计划是现在正在发生的事情。

106
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,520
Yes, let's break this phrase down.
是的，我们来分解这个短语。

107
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:39,480
So we've got stimulus package.
我们有“刺激计划”。

108
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:43,720
A stimulus package, something to stimulate the economy, right?
刺激计划，用来刺激经济的东西，对吧？

109
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:47,000
Right, so money from the government to get the economy moving.
对，就是政府投入资金让经济运转起来。

110
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,480
To get it moving, stimulus package.
让它运转起来，刺激计划。

111
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,480
Proposed.
提议的。

112
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,640
It means that it hasn't been approved yet.
意思是它还没有被批准。

113
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,640
Right, it's suggested.
对，是建议性的。

114
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:56,120
It's suggested, it's an idea.
是建议性的，是一个想法。

115
00:04:56,120 --> 00:05:01,640
So the proposed stimulus package for the US economy, for example, is $150 billion.
所以例如，美国经济的提议刺激计划是1500亿美元。

116
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:07,480
Right, that's $150 billion of American taxpayers' money that the government wants to pay.
对，那是1500亿美元的美国纳税人的钱，政府想要

117
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,480
Put into the economy to keep it moving.
投入经济中以保持其运转。

118
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,960
To keep it moving, right.
保持其运转，没错。

119
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:16,480
So if it works or not, that's still a debate, but it's a proposed stimulus package.
所以它是否有效，仍然有争议，但这是一项提议的刺激计划。

120
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:20,720
Let's move to our third phrase, aggregate demand.
让我们转到第三个短语：总需求。

121
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,880
Aggregate demand.
总需求。

122
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,580
Aggregate demand.
总需求。

123
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:24,580
Aggregate demand.
总需求。

124
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:28,560
So demand is pretty clear, but this word aggregate, what's that about?
需求这个词很清楚，但“总”是什么意思呢？

125
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:31,320
Aggregate is like a combined, added.
“总”就是合并、加总的意思。

126
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,320
Yeah.
对。

127
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,320
Right?
对吧？

128
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,320
Yeah.
嗯。

129
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,320
Aggregate demand.
总需求。

130
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:42,840
So like China, where cities like in Shanghai or cities like Beijing, where more and more
就像中国，像上海或北京这样的城市，越来越多

131
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:46,680
people are accumulating wealth, the aggregate demand is increasing.
的人积累财富，总需求在增加。

132
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,680
Right, right.
对，对。

133
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,920
The combined demand for consumer goods is growing.
对消费品的总需求在增长。

134
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:51,920
Right.
对。

135
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,640
More people have more money, so they're spending more.
更多的人有更多的钱，所以他们花得更多。

136
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:55,640
Yes.
是的。

137
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,640
Okay.
好的。

138
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:59,960
You know, Marco, there's a ton of excellent language in this dialogue, isn't there?
你知道吗，Marco，这段对话里有很多精彩的语言，对吧？

139
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,680
Yeah, a lot of good stuff here.
是的，这里有很多好东西。

140
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,680
Yeah.
嗯。

141
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:07,400
So let's listen to the dialogue one more time, but before we do, we have three words for
那我们再听一遍对话，但在听之前，我们想让你注意三个词。

142
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,440
you that we want you to listen for.
对。

143
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,440
Yeah.
注意这些词。

144
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,160
Pay attention to these words.
注意这些词。

145
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,160
Nest egg.
储备金。

146
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,800
Nest egg.
储备金。

147
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,800
Inevitable.
不可避免的。

148
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,800
Inevitable.
不可避免的。

149
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,640
And hit up.
还有“找某人要”。

150
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,640
Hit up.
找某人要。

151
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:24,960
So from the context of the dialogue, try and see if you can figure out what they mean,
所以根据对话的上下文，试着看看你是否能猜出它们的意思，

152
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:33,480
but after listening to it, we'll come back and explain it anyways.
但听完之后，我们还是会回来解释的。

153
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:37,720
Dad, I'd like to borrow some money.
爸爸，我想借点钱。

154
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,720
Sure, Johnny.
当然，Johnny。

155
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:39,720
How much do you need?
你需要多少？

156
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:40,720
Five bucks?
五块钱？

157
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,720
Come on, Dad.
拜托，爸爸。

158
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,720
I need $30,000.
我需要三万美元。

159
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,520
I want to get into the market.
我想进入市场。

160
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:48,320
You know, I'm tired of hearing all this news about the economic downturn, the inevitable
你知道，我厌倦了听到所有这些关于经济衰退、不可避免的

161
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:51,080
recession, people stuffing their money in their mattresses.
经济衰退，人们把钱都塞在床垫底下。

162
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:52,960
I look at this as an opportunity.
我把这看作是一个机会。

163
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:55,440
This is a chance for me to get a jumpstart on building my nest egg.
这是我提前开始攒钱的好机会。

164
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,960
I don't know about that.
我可不敢苟同。

165
00:06:56,960 --> 00:07:00,200
With all the uncertainty in the markets right now, it would be a very unwise decision to
鉴于目前市场的不确定性，现在投资是非常不明智的。

166
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,200
invest.
投资。

167
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:06,280
I don't know if you're aware, son, but there has been a lot of turmoil in the markets recently.
孩子，我不知道你是否意识到，最近市场动荡很大。

168
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:10,600
There have already been half a million layoffs in the last few months, and we have no idea
过去几个月已经有50万人失业，我们也不知道

169
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:14,240
how the proposed stimulus package will impact upon the economy.
拟议的经济刺激方案会对经济产生什么影响。

170
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,840
There's just too much instability.
太不稳定了。

171
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:18,640
I just wouldn't feel comfortable investing in this climate.
在这种环境下投资，我会觉得很不踏实。

172
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,360
But look at it this way.
但你可以这样看。

173
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,040
Every challenge is an opportunity.
每个挑战都是机遇。

